                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d606">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">693.116/66: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Minister in China (<persName type="to">Johnson</persName>)</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-07-22T14:00:00-04:00"
                            >July 22, 1933—2 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>257. Your 610, July 21, 9 a.m. and 617, July 22, 9 a.m. in regard to the
                    restrictions imposed by the Canton authorities upon the importation of liquid
                    fuel.</p>
                <p>A representative of the Standard Oil Company called at Department on July 21 in
                    regard to this matter. Department desires that the Legation and the Consul
                    General continue to press this matter both at Nanking and Canton as one of
                    importance and urgency.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Carr</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
